<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<!--
Hardened Runtime entitlements for the bundled Python sidecar.

Empirically reduced during Track C C0 (18 Apr 2026).

Load-bearing: ONLY com.apple.security.cs.disable-library-validation.
  Reason (post-C2, Apr 2026): even with the whole bundle signed under a
  single Apple Distribution identity (Z56GZVA2QB), PyInstaller's bundled
  Python.framework carries a nested internal identifier, and some third-
  party .so files retain signatures from their upstream wheels. Library
  validation blocks those dlopen sites with "mapping process and mapped
  file have different Team IDs". A full remove-then-resign cycle across
  every inner Mach-O followed by an exercised pipeline run is the planned
  retest that could allow dropping this entitlement —
  see ~/.claude/plans/c3-empty-ents-retest.md.

NOT needed for serve-only scope (confirmed by empty-entitlement test,
Python 3.12 + mlx_whisper, Apr 2026):
  - cs.allow-unsigned-executable-memory: CPython 3.12 does not use W+X.
  - cs.allow-jit: ctranslate2 is excluded; MLX uses Metal GPU kernels, not CPU JIT.
  - cs.allow-dyld-environment-variables: not required for serve.

C3 credential path (Apr 2026): the sidecar does NOT access macOS Keychain.
The Swift host reads Keychain via Security.framework and passes API keys
as BRISTLENOSE_*_API_KEY env vars at subprocess launch. No keychain-access-
groups or Security.framework entitlement needed on this side.

If a future addition needs any of the above, document the trigger here.
App Sandbox + user-facing entitlements (files, network, bookmarks) are
Track A's concern — the sidecar will add com.apple.security.inherit at
that point so the parent's sandbox applies.
-->
<plist version="1.0">
<dict>
    <key>com.apple.security.cs.disable-library-validation</key>
    <true/>
</dict>
</plist>
